M|skills|source-principles: principles.md v1.0 — if cnt diverges, principles.md is canonical. Run skills-sync after any edit to principles.md.
M|skills|> Fast activation. Sharp output. Built for soc posts, product copy,
M|skills|> quick cg decisions, and any cnt needed without a long ses.
M|skills|> Claude reasons quickly but never skips the brand intake or feedback loop.
M|skills|Before generating a single word of cnt, Claude MUST:
M|skills|1. Read `BRAND_MEMORY.md` for the relevant brand
M|skills|2. Read `STRATEGY_LOG.md` — find the last 3 entries for this surface type
M|skills|3. Check `LEVER_TRACKER.md` — is any lever at Triple Cap (used 3x in a row)?
M|skills|4. Run the Pre-cnt Checklist (Step 1)
M|skills|If brand mem file does not exist → STOP. Ask Stark to fill it before proceeding.
M|skills|Never work anonymously. Never assume brand ctx.
M|skills|> Run this AFTER loading brand ctx (Step 0). Answer before selecting any layer.
M|skills|> This is Kahneman's core framework — every piece of cnt targets one system primarily.
M|skills|**Answer the routing question:**
M|skills|| Question | System 1 | System 2 |
M|skills||---|---|---|
M|skills|| Speed of audience dec | Instant — gut, scroll-stop, emotional | Deliberate — comparing, researching, justifying |
M|skills|| cnt goal | Stop the scroll, create feeling, build desire | Explain, convince, resolve objection |
M|skills|| Funnel stage | Discovery, awareness, re-engagement | Consideration, dec, post-purchase |
M|skills|**Route:**
M|skills|- **System 1 cnt** → Lead with L1 (Perception), L2 (Desire), L6 (Attention/Spread)
M|skills|- **System 2 cnt** → Lead with L3 (Influence/Persuasion), L4 (Behavioral Economics)
M|skills|- **System 1 → System 2 transition** (moving someone from scroll to dec) → L2 + L3 bridge
M|skills|State your route before proceeding to Step 1. Do not skip.
M|skills|Answer these before activating any layer:
M|skills|| Question | Answer |
M|skills||---|---|
M|skills|| Which brand? | |
M|skills|| Which surface? (soc / website / product / email / ad / cg) | |
M|skills|| cnt goal? (acquire / retain / deepen loyalty) | |
M|skills|| Is this System 1 cnt? (gut-feel, scroll-stop, instant emotion) | |
M|skills|| Or System 2? (deliberate, considered, research-mode) | |
M|skills|| soc signal or self-signal? (showing others vs validating self) | |
M|skills|| Brand lifecycle stage? (0→1 / growing / scaling / repositioning) | |
M|skills|| Any lever at Triple Cap right now? | |
M|skills|Read the last 3 STRATEGY_LOG entries for this brand + surface.
M|skills|**If previous str exists:**
M|skills|- Did it work? (check Results field)
M|skills|- YES → identify the mechanism, evolve it, check Triple Cap
M|skills|- NO → diagnose why (wrong lever? wrong surface? wrong timing?), select new lever
M|skills|- PENDING → note it, proceed with new cnt, flag that results are still outstanding
M|skills|**If no previous entry:**
M|skills|- Fresh start. Full layer reasoning below.
M|skills|**Triple Cap Rule:**
M|skills|If the same psychological lever has been the PRIMARY driver 3 consecutive times
M|skills|for the same brand surface → it is CAPPED. Select a different lever.
M|skills|Claude must not override this rule even if the lever is performing well.
M|skills|Variety maintains psychological freshness in the audience's mind.
M|skills|Claude activates the most relevant 2-3 layers per piece of cnt.
M|skills|Not all layers fire every time. Choose based on surface + goal.
M|skills|*Activates when: website copy, product pages, first-touch soc cnt, ads*
M|skills|**Core mechanism:** The brain decides in milliseconds. Before logic fires,
M|skills|the subconscious has already judged. cnt must pass this filter first.
M|skills|**Key principles:**
M|skills|- Processing fluency — easier to process = more trusted. Simplicity signals quality.
M|skills|- Halo effect — one strong positive cue colors everything else
M|skills|- Thin-slicing — people form accurate impressions from tiny amounts of information
M|skills|- Pattern interrupt — break expected format to force attention
M|skills|**Activation trigger:** Ask — *what does someone feel in the first 2 seconds?*
M|skills|If the answer is "nothing" — this layer needs work before anything else.
M|skills|**Research prompt (runtime):** Search current examples of brands in this
M|skills|category using silence, minimalism, or visual contrast as perception tools.
M|skills|*Activates when: product descriptions, cg hooks, brand storytelling*
M|skills|**Core mechanism:** People don't buy products. They buy who they want to become.
M|skills|The gap between current self and aspirational self is the engine of desire.
M|skills|**Key principles:**
M|skills|- Jobs-to-be-Done — what progress is the customer trying to make in their life?
M|skills|- Identity-based desire — "people like me wear/use/buy this"
M|skills|- Aspirational self gap — show the future version, not the current product
M|skills|- Authenticity signal — desire built on false promises collapses; on truth, compounds
M|skills|**Activation trigger:** Ask — *who does the customer become after buying this?*
M|skills|That answer is the cnt. The product is just the vehicle.
M|skills|**Research prompt (runtime):** Search how small independent brands in this
M|skills|category have used founder story or customer transformation as their primary hook.
M|skills|*Activates when: CTAs, launch cnt, limited releases, soc proof moments*
M|skills|**Cialdini's 7 — activation map:**
M|skills|| Principle | When to use | When NOT to use |
M|skills||---|---|---|
M|skills|| Reciprocity | Give value before asking | Don't force it — feels transactional |
M|skills|| Commitment | Post-purchase loyalty cnt | Early acquisition — too soon |
M|skills|| soc proof | Mid-funnel, consideration stage | Brand new launches — no proof yet |
M|skills|| Authority | tec or quality claims | Casual/lifestyle cnt — kills vibe |
M|skills|| Liking | Brand voice, community cnt | Hard sell moments |
M|skills|| Scarcity | Drops, limited editions, deadlines | Everyday products — loses meaning |
M|skills|| Unity | Community, shared identity cnt | Broad audiences — too generic |
M|skills|**Activation trigger:** Ask — *which principle is this cnt trying to activate?*
M|skills|Never activate more than 2 simultaneously — audiences feel manipulated.
M|skills|*Activates when: pricing cnt, product tiers, checkout experience, offer framing*
M|skills|**Key principles (compressed):**
M|skills|- Loss aversion — "don't miss" outperforms "you'll gain" by ~2x
M|skills|- Anchoring — first price/value seen sets the reference frame for everything after
M|skills|- Decoy effect — 3-tier pricing makes the middle tier feel like the smart choice
M|skills|- Paradox of choice — fewer options = higher conversion
M|skills|- Peak-end rule — people remember the peak moment and the ending, not the average
M|skills|**Activation trigger:** Ask — *is this cnt about a dec?*
M|skills|If yes, frame around what they lose by not acting, not what they gain by acting.
M|skills|*Activates when: brand identity cnt, visual direction, cg naming, tone*
M|skills|**Key principles:**
M|skills|- Mental availability (Byron Sharp) — be thought of first in the buying moment
M|skills|- Distinctive assets — one repeatable visual/verbal signature beats many varied ones
M|skills|- Emotional encoding — stories are remembered; specs are forgotten
M|skills|- Archetype alignment — brand personality should map to one Jungian archetype
M|skills|consistently (Rebel, Creator, Lover, Hero, Sage, Innocent, Explorer, Ruler)
M|skills|**Activation trigger:** Ask — *if someone saw this with no logo, would they know
M|skills|it was this brand?* If no — this layer needs work.
M|skills|*Activates when: soc cnt, hooks, viral mechanics, cg structure*
M|skills|**Key principles:**
M|skills|- Curiosity gap — open a loop the audience needs to close ("here's what we found...")
M|skills|- Zeigarnik effect — unfinished things are remembered (never complete the story in post 1)
M|skills|- Von Restorff — the thing that's different gets remembered
M|skills|- Emotional contagion — high-arousal emotions (awe, excitement, outrage) spread 3x more
M|skills|- Pattern interrupt — break the expected format in the first 2 seconds
M|skills|**Activation trigger:** Ask — *why would someone share this?*
M|skills|If there's no answer — it won't spread regardless of quality.
M|skills|**Research prompt (runtime):** Search recent examples of small brands
M|skills|that generated outsized reach with minimal spend. Extract the mechanism, not the execution.
M|skills|*Activates when: community cnt, brand positioning, cultural moments, identity cg*
M|skills|**Key principles:**
M|skills|- In-group/out-group — belonging to "us" requires knowing who "them" is
M|skills|- Tribal identity signals — language, aesthetics, and references that mark membership
M|skills|- Status signaling — in fashion specifically, products signal aspiration hierarchy
M|skills|- Cultural congruence — cnt that feels out of sync with current cultural moment fails
M|skills|regardless of psychological soundness
M|skills|**Activation trigger:** Ask — *what group does this cnt make someone feel part of?*
M|skills|And — *is that the group this brand is building?*
M|skills|**Timing & ctx note:** When cnt is delivered matters as much as what it says.
M|skills|A launch post, a mid-scroll organic post, and a retargeting touchpoint are
M|skills|psychologically different events requiring different lever activation.
M|skills|Always produce exactly 2 variants. Each tests a DIFFERENT psychological lever.
M|skills|Never produce 2 variants that are just tonal rewrites of the same lever.
M|skills|**Variant A:**
M|skills|- Primary lever: [state which layer and which principle]
M|skills|- Rationale: [one sentence — why this lever for this brand at this stage]
M|skills|- cnt: [the actual output]
M|skills|**Variant B:**
M|skills|- Primary lever: [state which layer and which principle]
M|skills|- Rationale: [one sentence — why this is a meaningfully different psychological test]
M|skills|- cnt: [the actual output]
M|skills|**Run recommendation:** [Which to run first and why — based on brand lifecycle stage
M|skills|and what's been tried before per str Log]
M|skills|Before delivering, Claude checks:
M|skills|- [ ] Does this pass the 2-second System 1 filter?
M|skills|- [ ] Is the psychological lever intentional and named?
M|skills|- [ ] Is it consistent with Brand mem File?
M|skills|- [ ] Does it serve the brand's desired perception — not undermine it?
M|skills|- [ ] Is the Triple Cap Rule respected?
M|skills|- [ ] Are both variants testing genuinely different levers?
M|skills|If any box fails — revise before delivering.
M|skills|Claude generates the following entries. Stark pastes them into the correct files, or MCP filesystem tool writes them if configured.
M|skills|```
M|skills|Date: [auto]
M|skills|Brand: [brand name]
M|skills|Surface: [soc / website / product / email / ad / cg]
M|skills|Goal: [acquire / retain / deepen loyalty]
