M|skills|Triple Cap status: [lever name — count X/3]
M|skills|Results: [PENDING]
M|skills|Diagnosis: [fill when results come in]
M|skills|Next cycle direction: [fill when results come in]
M|skills|```
M|skills|Add one row to the relevant brand + surface table:
M|skills|```
M|skills|| [N] | [YYYY-MM-DD] | [primary lever name] | L[1-7] | [ACTIVE / CAPPED] |
M|skills|```
M|skills|Update Cap Status Summary. If count = 3 → mark CAPPED, alert in output.
M|skills|Add one line to the brand's BRAND_MEMORY.md audience psychology section:
M|skills|```
M|skills|[YYYY-MM-DD] Psychology note: [what was observed about this audience's rsp to lever X on surface Y]
M|skills|```
M|skills|This builds a compounding brand-specific psychological profile across sessions.
M|skills|Add one line to the agt mem.md:
M|skills|```
M|skills|[YYYY-MM-DD] — STRATEGY_LOG entry written: [brand] / [surface] / [primary lever] — [outcome: PENDING]
M|skills|```
M|skills|After all writes → if previous cycle Results field is filled → run `@kahneman results` to trigger proposal.
M|skills|When this skill calls for a research prompt:
M|skills|1. Search for current real-world brand examples (not older than 18 months)
M|skills|2. Find both large AND small brand examples — weight small brands equally
M|skills|3. Extract: what happened → what psychological mechanism drove it →
M|skills|what would need to be true for it to work for this brand
M|skills|4. Never reference examples directly in output ("like X did") —
M|skills|extract the mechanism and apply it natively
M|skills|5. Discard examples that don't have a clear psychological mechanism behind them
M|skills|The same psychological lever cannot be the PRIMARY driver for more than
M|skills|3 consecutive pieces of cnt on the same brand surface.
M|skills|Tracking lives in `LEVER_TRACKER.md` per brand per surface.
M|skills|**Why this rule exists:**
M|skills|Audiences psychologically adapt. A lever that worked 3 times will produce
M|skills|diminishing returns on the 4th. The brand's cnt starts feeling predictable.
M|skills|Predictable = invisible. Invisible = no impact.
M|skills|**What counts as "same lever":**
M|skills|Same Cialdini principle, same layer, same core psychological mechanism.
M|skills|Evolving the execution (different copy, different visual) does NOT reset the cap.
M|skills|Only switching the PRIMARY lever resets it.
M|skills|**Cap reset:**
M|skills|After using a different primary lever once, the previous lever's cap resets.
M|skills|*Variant A is optimized for speed. When a task requires full strategic depth,
M|skills|cg architecture, or brand repositioning — use 02-kahneman.md instead.*
M|skills|> Kahneman appends one line here after each ses when results are confirmed (not PENDING).
M|skills|> Over time this builds brand-specific psychological intelligence. Do not edit manually.
